b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Figma AI is best suited for UI/UX designers, design teams, product teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Uizard, meanwhile, shines for product managers, non designers, rapid prototyping, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Figma AI describes itself as \"Professional UI design tool with AI-powered design assistance features.\" Uizard, established in 2018, positions itself as \"AI-powered UI design tool that turns ideas into interactive prototypes.\" With 6 years between them, Figma AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Uizard offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Figma AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Uizard is a poor choice — far from it. Uizard excels in its own right, particularly for product managers and non designers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value industry-standard ui design tool, go with Figma AI. If generate ui from text descriptions matters more to you, Uizard is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
